  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Asset-based development workflows are inserted into your existing software development processes. Many of the same&#xD;
    tools the enterprise uses to conduct software development will still be used. The major difference is the nature of the&#xD;
    content for those tools, its structure, and who is working with it will change.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Development time&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Reusable asset repository: this tool is critical for asset-based development. There are several key capabilities to&#xD;
        consider to support the enterprise. Some of these include:&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Authentication and access control&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Custom asset review workflows&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Repository configuration for asset types and classification schemas&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Integration with development tools&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Integration with other repositories and registries&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Asset usage measurement and cost analysis&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Impact analysis&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Testing tools&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Configuration Management&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Workflow Management&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Change Management&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Portfolio Data Warehouse&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IDE&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Runtime&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Configuration Management&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Service Registry&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>As a last step you need to evaluate the scenarios which will include the tools and determine what modifications and&#xD;
extensions are required.</mainDescription>
